        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 8:09PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 809 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Sabinal, or 16 miles southwest of Hondo, moving
south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sabinal and Knippa.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
